  "title": "filter not being properly applied in federated search",
  "body": "<!--\r\n  Thanks for participating in this project! We will try to answer as soon as possible 🙏\r\n-->\r\n\r\n**Describe the bug 🐛**\r\nA facet filter is not applied to another index.\r\n\r\n**To Reproduce 🔍**\r\nSteps to reproduce the behavior:\r\n1. Go to https://codesandbox.io/s/ais-ecommerce-demo-app-6hxt7\r\n2. Click \"blue\" on the refinement list\r\n3. Confirm there're non-blue items on `banners` index.\r\n\r\n**Expected behavior 💭**\r\nThere should be only \"blue\" items.\r\n\r\n**Screenshots 🖥**\r\n\r\n![image](https://user-images.githubusercontent.com/499898/69816933-b76b1a80-11f9-11ea-89a7-0c3da7449e90.png)\r\n\r\n**Environment:**\r\nN/A\r\n\r\n**Additional context**\r\n```\r\nㄴ index `products`\r\n    ㄴ index `products`\r\n        ㄴ refinementList\r\n        ㄴ hits\r\n    ㄴ index `banners`\r\n        ㄴ hits\r\n```\r\n\r\nWhen \"blue\" is refined, it should apply to all the indices.",
